(46, 12, '', 'Goa Packages', '3N/4D', 'tripimage/76941293.jpg', '2021-11-14 00:00:00', '2021-11-20 00:00:00', 5, 'Goa', 'goa-packages', '7000', 1000, '1', '<p>The beautiful land of Goa has become India&rsquo;s favourite holiday destination ever since it gained its independence from the Portuguese. Rising to prominence with the boho and hipster culture, Goa tourism has achieved a legendary status over the years. Starting out as an exotic hippie town, the holiday experience of Goa has now evolved to match some of the best holiday destinations around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a rich history and an abundance of things to do, you can have a memorable holiday in Goa. The modern infrastructure complements the rich historical significance of this holiday destination extremely well. The people of Goa take immense pride in their heritage and history. In fact, most of Goa tourism concentrates on showcasing their history and preserving it for their future generations. Each Goa tourist place focuses on highlighting its culture and heritage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have been to Goa, it will carve its own place in your heart. You will keep coming back to replenish the well of your memories straight form the source. Pure and unadulterated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trust Goa tourism to take you on a magical ride every time you visit here.</p>\r\n', '2021-11-14 01:03:12', '2021-12-23 01:02:25', 1),
(47, 9, '', 'Andaman & Nicobar Packages', '5N/6D', 'tripimage/55835570.jpg', '2021-11-16 00:00:00', '2021-11-23 00:00:00', 5, 'Andaman & Nicobar', 'andaman-nicobar-packages', '11000', 1000, '1', '<p>Exotic, beautiful and richly evocative of India&rsquo;s colonial past, the Andaman and Nicobar Islands are growing into a popular tourist destination. The 2 groups of islands, made up of the summits of a submerged mountain range, form India&rsquo;s most remote state, located in the middle of the Bay of Bengal.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Andaman Nicobar tourism immediately evokes images of crystal-clear waters, rainbow-hued reefs and lush tropical forests. Besides, most Indians recall the infamous Kaala Pani or Cellular Jail, which is a major attraction of Andaman tourism today. Whether you&rsquo;re looking for a relaxed beach vacation or an adventurous holiday of trekking, snorkelling and scuba diving, you&rsquo;ll find that Andaman tourism has the charm of a holiday that&rsquo;s far from the madding crowd, yet close enough to the comforts of civilisation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2021-11-14 02:24:43', '2021-12-23 12:15:39', 1),
(48, 9, '1', 'Leh-Ladakh Packages', '6N/7D', 'tripimage/10099379.jpg', '2021-11-23 00:00:00', '2021-11-30 00:00:00', 5, 'Ladakh', 'leh-ladakh-packages', '20000', 1000, '1', '<p>The stark and glorious land of Ladakh is located in Jammu and Kashmir. Yet, it is so far removed from what one expects of Kashmir, both in terms of geography and culture. A Ladakh tour will show you a very different and awe-inspiring world. Ladakh itself is separated from the Kashmir valley by the Himalayan range and the difference is immense. The breath-taking landscape is almost magical. Ladakh is known to be the world&rsquo;s coldest desert. Here, you will find glaciers and sand dunes and freezing winds shaping the raw landscape.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Undoubtedly, you will emerge a changed person after your Ladakh tour. The people of Ladakh are friendly and there&rsquo;s a sense of spirituality in the air. You can sense it as soon as you enter Ladakh. The many Tibetan monasteries contribute to this. But the wide expanse of the sky, the land and the mountains make you realise how tiny and insignificant we are in the whole grand design of the universe. The land might be barren, but it comes alive with the people here whose love for their land and simple joys infuse the landscape with life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2021-11-14 02:29:08', '2021-12-23 12:19:26', 1),
(49, 9, '', 'Jammu & Kashmir Package', '8N/9D', 'tripimage/83566848.jpg', '2021-11-15 00:00:00', '2021-11-23 00:00:00', 5, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'jammu-kashmir-package', '18999', 1000, '1', '<p>Mughal emperor Jahangir is known to have referred to Kashmir as &lsquo;heaven on earth&rsquo; and he was absolutely correct. Anyone who visits this beautiful state will not dispute this fact because they will be stunned speechless by the ethereal beauty here. Soaring mountain ranges, crisp cool weather, lakes and snow and so much more to see here and do that you will wonder why you didn&rsquo;t come here before.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kashmir tourism has seen its ups and downs over the decades and now it&rsquo;s back in full force. Tourists are returning to the Valley with hope in their eyes so they too may experience a slice of heaven on earth. Jammu and Kashmir tourism begins in Srinagar and moves to Gulmarg, Sonmarg and Pahalgam along with Leh and Ladakh. Tourists can be found traipsing through the gorgeous Mughal Gardens in the evenings, while the Dal Lake is dotted with elegant shikharas cutting through the glass-like surface of the water as they transport visitors to another realm altogether.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2021-11-14 02:48:33', '2021-12-23 12:22:33', 1),
(50, 9, '', 'Kerala Packages', '9N/10D', 'tripimage/44622096.jpg', '2021-11-15 00:00:00', '2021-11-25 00:00:00', 5, 'Kerala', 'kerala-packages', '3999', 1000, '1', '<p>Known as the &ldquo;God&rsquo;s Own Country&rdquo;, Kerala is surely one of the most beautiful places in India. Kerala or Keralam is a Malayalee word made up of two parts; &lsquo;Kera&rsquo; meaning coconut and &lsquo;alam&rsquo; meaning land. The land of coconut trees is a destination that has something for every kind of traveller. Whether you want to sail the glistening backwaters or lose yourself in the mystical coastal greenery, Kerala is an ultimate tourist destination to experience bliss and serenity.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cooming soon</p>\r\n', '2021-11-14 02:57:31', '2021-12-23 12:27:56', 1),
(52, 10, '2', 'Himachal Pradesh Packages', '3 days', 'tripimage/97082481.jpg', '2021-11-15 00:00:00', '2021-11-23 00:00:00', 5, 'Shimla, Kullu, Manali, Chamba, Dalhousie, Dharamshala)', 'himachal-pradesh-packages', '6500', 6200, '1', '<p>Himachal Pradesh is tourist hub of India. The beautiful hill stations and landscapes of the Great Himalayas make it one of the most popular destinations among the visitors. The cold weather, mighty rivers, the snows peak of mountains, the lush green forests and many religious temples make Himachal Pradesh a complete place and first pick of travellers, as it offers everything for all age groups of people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Himachal has a lot to offer to adventure lovers. Outdoor activities like mountain biking, paragliding, ice skating, river rafting, heli-skiing, rock climbing and many more activities keep your adrenaline rush high. The rich diversity of flora and fauna are soul fulfilling. The flower carpet meadows are a soothing relief to the eyes.&nbsp; Trekking on hilly terrain with lush green forest and snow during winters is a lifetime experience. Watching tall trees through the road trips is eye soothing. Himachal Pradesh never fails to charm you with its magnificent beauty. Temples, monasteries, churches are another attraction for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Himachal Pradesh tourism has led to significant development of the state. Travellers can enjoy a very comfortable stay at the hotels, which are in plenty.&nbsp; Himachal is nothing less than a heaven on earth where you can relax and feel rejuvenated.&nbsp;Just pack your bags and prepare yourself to explore the marvelous Himachal Pradesh with DreamMyTrip Holidays&#39;</p>\r\n', '2021-11-15 17:46:02', '2021-12-23 01:00:34', 1),
(53, 9, '1,2', 'Uttarakhand Packages', '5N/6D', 'tripimage/20132328.jpg', '2021-11-16 00:00:00', '2021-11-22 00:00:00', 5, 'Haridwar, Badrinath, Kedarnath, and Gangotri', 'uttarakhand-packaegs', '11999', 1000, '1', '<p>Dev Bhoomi &ndash; Land of Gods &ndash; Uttarakhand is a captivating place that is a religious and spiritual destination. For adventure seekers, go off the beaten track. The winding roads lead you to rugged landscapes that offers adrenaline pumping activities like bungee jumping, mountain biking, white water rafting, paragliding, trekking, and much more. The colonial rule is evident in its hill stations and the legacy left behind at Jim Corbett National Park (one of the highest populations of tigers). The natural beauty of Uttarakhand is a refreshing change that soothes the eyes, energises the body, and lightens the mind.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Things to Do in Uttarakhand</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The snowclad mountains, rising above the plains, unleashes water into flowing rivers. The gushing streams are the fodder of thick, tall trees rising from the mountains. The azure lakes are havens of enchantment. This rocky landscape forms the state of Uttarakhand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For centuries, Hindus have traversed the mountains to visit Haridwar, Badrinath, Kedarnath, and Gangotri. While travellers have sought peace at Rishikesh. In recent year, Uttarakhand has become one of the most popular destinations for adventure seekers. The tough terrain has attracted Indians to engage in white water rafting, skiing, trekking, and mountain climbing. Many biker groups are turning their attention to Uttarakhand. The state offers challenging and fun destinations that have breath taking views. There are many things to do in Uttarakhand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The weather is amazing, almost all the months in the year, and the scenery is just what you need to forget worldly problems. Appreciate nature as you go on an Uttarakhand sightseeing trip.</p>\r\n', '2021-11-15 17:48:18', '2021-12-23 12:29:39', 1),
(54, 9, '2', 'Rajasthan Packages', '4N/5D', 'tripimage/53946231.jpg', '2021-12-31 00:00:00', '2021-12-31 00:00:00', 5, 'Jodhpur, Jaipur, Ajmer, Jaisalmer, Mount Abu', 'rajasthan-packages', '10999', 1000, '1', '<p>India&rsquo;s most colourful destination is found in its desert state, Rajasthan. With a unique geography, a long-lasting royal history and a vibrant local culture, it is truly one of the country&rsquo;s gems when it comes to tourism for national and international visitors alike. A Rajasthan tour can take you anywhere from lively bazaars to epic sand dunes to exquisite forts and palaces, from one town to the next. And not to mention the wildlife spotting opportunities, monuments to go sightseeing and a host of spirited festivals that will leave you thrilled.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re looking for to experience the royal treatment, there&rsquo;s no place better in all of India than the land of Maharajas. Spend your days by a sunny lake, under symmetrical palace archways, watching over brightly painted towns, on a lively jungle safari and devouring generations-old recipes. While nights couldn&rsquo;t be any better, soaking in a folk performance or dining al fresco under a canopy of stars. Rajasthan tourism promises to leave you feeling enchanted, enlightened and full of eclectic experiences to carry back home</p>\r\n', '2021-11-15 21:30:09', '2022-01-26 08:17:06', 1),
